column11: This question was closed on option "All of the above will survive season 6" with an end date of 23 October 2016. The season 7 premier revealed that all of the characters listed in this question survived season 6. “[The midseason premiere] is a huge turning point for Rick and the group, because there’s a lot of chaos and it’s very brutal,” says executive producer and creator Robert Kirkman. 4/15/16: The finale of the Walking Dead's Season 6 left us with a cliffhanger and an unresolved question: Did someone die at the end of the episode and, if so, who? We've decided to keep the question open until the answer to that question is revealed. We'll close the question once we know the identity of anyone who died at the end of Season 6 and all forecasts made until closing will count. If it becomes clear that none of the characters listed in the question died in Season 6, then we'll resolve on option F. Recommended Questions Will Winds of Winter be released before Season 6 of Game of Thrones airs? Which movie will win the Oscar for Best Picture?

Probability should be near 0% for Michonne, but the writers here are terrible, which makes them a bit unpredictable (yes, they might actually kill off another black character despite serious issues with this from past seasons, and giving up on great comic book material). Given the cast's reactions to the scene, I think it is Daryl, despite knowledge from the comic books that it might be Glenn. So I've split between those two characters, favoring Daryl as the victim. Say it isn't so, though, because I love Daryl's character (as well as Glenn's). Whoever it is, it will be hard to see.
